# Vibe Coding

When this rule applies (files under `Docs/` are in context):

1. Follow the project skill **vibe-coding-workflow** (`.cursor/skills/vibe-coding-workflow/SKILL.md`): Clarify + confirm landing details → write/update `{TaskName}_Plan.md` → implement while appending `{TaskName}_Progress.md`.
2. Cross-task roadmap: **`Docs/SprintPlan.md`**. Architecture intent: **`Docs/EngineArchitecture.md`** (both git-tracked under `Docs/`). When either file changes, keep the other aligned per **`docs-roadmap-arch-sync.mdc`** (same change set unless user waives).
3. **SprintPlan hygiene:** active sprints list only open `[ ]` tasks. When done, **move the task line** to `## Archived` with sprint tag (`[S0]`…`[S8]`, `[parallel]`); do not leave `[x]` in active sections. Keep `{TaskName}_Plan.md` / `_Progress.md` at **`Docs/` root for the current sprint** — do not move them to `Archived/plans/` on task close.
4. Do not skip clarification for new tasks unless the user explicitly waives it.
5. Implementation changes must remain traceable in `_Progress.md` after each completed plan step or coherent batch of work.
6. Before closing a task: run **build / smoke-run** per the skill (or document N/A in plan + progress). Smoke commands: **`vulkan-smoke-test.mdc`**, **`Docs/CLI.md`**.
7. If implementation deviates from `{TaskName}_Plan.md`, apply the deviation handling protocol in the skill before continuing.
